text: Sintjohannesga () is a village in De Fryske Marren municipality in the province of Friesland, the Netherlands. It had a population of around 1280 in 2017.Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2017 - CBS There is a windmill in the village, De Hersteller. ==History== Before 2014, Sintjohannesga was part of the Skarsterlân municipality and before 1984 it was part of Haskerland. Before 1934, Sintjohannesga was part of the Schoterland municipality. ==References== ==External links== Category:De Fryske Marren Category:Populated places in Friesland
